comments[23]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T14:35:43.038Z",codex-root,"Implementation start 2026-07-18: all-status duplicate review found this canonical transaction gap and no competing atomic multi-item plus relationship-event item. Scope is a public SDK transaction journal, failure injection, recovery, immutable compensation semantics, and VCS acceptance migration."
  "2026-07-18T15:19:21.122Z",codex-root,"Implementation evidence 2026-07-18: added public commitWorkspaceTransaction with a durable per-workspace journal, one writer lock, ordered idempotent inspection/application, deterministic replay, reverse append-style compensation, explicit crash interruption semantics, extension-host binding, and public SDK export. pm-vcs merge is the non-PM consumer and binds transaction identity to changeset+ref. Verification: 5,914 tests across 311 files at exact 100/100/100/100 (39,043 statements; 27,456 branches; 7,949 functions; 38,008 lines); lint/zero-clone/static/docstring/package-boundary/token/audit gates clean. Packed temp consumer committed+replayed the SDK transaction and completed VCS ref/create/propose/merge/log plus deep doctor at /tmp/pm-sdk-transaction-proof-P5Bp3l. Release gates passed through packed smoke and 88-command dogfood; only the expected pre-commit Greptile stage remained."
  "2026-07-18T15:36:41.210Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review b4db10ed-d5b4-4ff0-84b3-ba2ee8f3209a (confidence 3/5, five findings) was fully accepted: result-free apply now has an honest undefined return contract; callers can configure positive lock TTL/wait bounds; the journal is read once per attempt; VCS SDK host access is guarded with a descriptive error; and the compensation race test uses a new semantic step_compensating transition instead of storage-call ordinals. Post-fix full verification: 311 files / 5,914 tests, exact 100/100/100/100 (39,051 statements; 27,460 branches; 7,951 functions; 38,017 lines), typecheck, ESLint, zero clones, static/docstrings, package boundary, and token budget all pass."
  "2026-07-18T15:45:51.663Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile re-review 3f2f3c62-2f59-431f-8c53-252a24c151d0 completed at confidence 5/5 with no comments and explicitly verified all five first-round findings resolved. Exact full coverage, strict lint/static gates, and packed SDK+VCS acceptance remain clean on the corrected code."
  "2026-07-18T16:49:47.732Z",codex-root,"Hosted PR #605 review round 1 evidence: accepted eight valid recovery/compensation findings and declined one pm-docs false positive with live metadata proof. Hardened runtime input types, journal lifecycle invariants, null-prototype result maps, inspection-authoritative recovery, VCS original-ref restoration, transaction-owned compensation, retry event identity, and item+relationship post-commit validation. All nine inline threads were reacted to, answered contextually, and resolved; Gemini, Greptile, CodeRabbit, Codecov, CodSpeed, and Sourcery artifacts were individually reacted to and acknowledged. Verification: linked pm tests passed; 311 files / 5,916 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (39,078 statements, 27,482 branches, 7,957 functions, 38,043 lines); lint, zero clones, static complexity, 100% docstrings, package boundary, token budget, secrets, audit, and packed VCS+SDK replay at /tmp/pm-sdk-transaction-review-proof-bM6GcR all pass."
  "2026-07-18T17:14:56.466Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 83e0a668-645f-4229-89fe-889358d7a38e found one valid P1: compensation discovery could throw before persisting compensating state, leaving an applying journal without an automatic reconciliation path. Reopened only this canonical transaction item for the focused recovery-state correction."
  "2026-07-18T17:21:26.774Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile 83e0a668 P1 resolved: compensation now writes durable compensating state before any domain inspection, reconciles all steps in reverse order, and invokes each step's idempotent transaction-owned compensation when inspection itself fails. A regression reproduces an inspection conflict after an earlier step applied, verifies the journal reaches compensated without manual deletion, clears the conflict, and proves the next attempt commits. Verification: focused 14 tests pass, strict static/docstring/package/token gates pass, and full repository coverage passes 311 files / 5,917 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 (39,077 statements, 27,480 branches, 7,957 functions, 38,043 lines)."
  "2026-07-18T17:29:11.887Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile re-review 5e788dee-5f3f-4ee8-b7af-9d5929480d35 completed at confidence 5/5 with no comments. It explicitly confirmed the prior stuck-journal defect is closed: compensating state is durable before inspection, inspection errors reconcile rather than abort, VCS guards touch only exact forward mutations, and compensated retries advance without manual deletion."
  "2026-07-18T17:38:56.198Z",codex-root,"Hosted round 2 evidence: CI typecheck caught the VCS committed-state helper accepting a complete ItemMetadata while the SDK correctly returns a partial projection. Greptile also reproduced a relationship-conflict path where item compensation could revert a committed merge discovered before this attempt. Reopened only pm-4e12 while correcting both ownership and contract invariants."
  "2026-07-18T17:56:40.172Z",codex-root,"Hosted round 2 repairs complete: corrected the partial ItemMetadata helper contract and gated item compensation on a marker set only after this invocation performs the merge write. Added a regression proving an already-merged changeset remains merged when a conflicting latest relationship event aborts reconciliation. Gemini's close_reason/closed_at suggestion was declined after verifying the public unset token is close-reason and terminal-to-proposed update already clears closed_at including null. All four threads were reacted to, answered inline, and resolved. Verification: typecheck root/packages/examples passes; focused 14 tests pass; 311 files / 5,917 tests pass at exact 100/100/100/100 (39,082 statements, 27,482 branches, 7,958 functions, 38,047 lines); ESLint, zero clones, complexity, 100% docstrings, SDK boundary, and token budget pass."
  "2026-07-18T18:16:56.288Z",codex-root,"Exact-code pre-push Greptile review 1f2e6ad5-b0a3-43d9-9fef-12d41f38b319 completed at confidence 5/5 with zero comments. It explicitly confirmed attempt-owned VCS compensation and the latestConflict regression close the prior-merge corruption path, the partial metadata contract is correct, and the branch is safe to merge. Two possible observability simplifications were noted as non-findings with no correctness or compensation-safety impact."
  "2026-07-18T18:23:00.229Z",codex-root,"Hosted round 3 accepted findings: Greptile identified that process-local VCS ownership is lost after apply-before-journal-record crashes; Gemini identified partial in-memory journal result mutation if a later inspection throws and an unsafe ENOENT property cast. Scope is a public durable per-step provenance contract plus atomic discovery and safe error narrowing, with VCS crash acceptance."
  "2026-07-18T18:41:38.528Z",codex-root,"Hosted round 3 repairs complete: the public transaction journal now records startedStepIds before invoking apply and atomically stores prepareCompensation JSON data required to restore pre-mutation state after process restart. Compensation is restricted to transaction-started steps and receives durable data; VCS no longer uses process-local ownership. discoverAppliedSteps swaps a temporary result map only after every inspection succeeds, and ENOENT narrowing is safe for unknown throws. New acceptance covers apply-before-record crash + later ledger conflict + original-ref restoration, pre-existing merge preservation, malformed compensation data, atomic discovery failure/retry, and inspection failure during owned compensation. Verification: focused 15 tests; 311 files / 5,918 tests exact 100/100/100/100 (39,105 statements, 27,502 branches, 7,967 functions, 38,072 lines); typecheck, ESLint, zero clones, complexity, 100% docstrings, SDK boundary, token budget pass. Packed proof /tmp/pm-sdk-durable-compensation-proof-hsDup4 installed the tarball and local pm-vcs, completed ref/create/propose/merge/log, restored packed compensation pre-state, and passed isolated deep package doctor with zero warnings/blockers."
  "2026-07-18T18:58:23.767Z",codex-root,"Exact-code pre-push Greptile review completed at confidence 5/5 with zero comments on a272a2ea. It confirmed started-step provenance is durable before apply, compensation data is atomically journaled, discovery is buffered until all inspections succeed, compensation cannot leave the journal stuck, VCS crash recovery restores original state, and the branch is safe to merge. Four P2 observations were explicitly non-blocking and produced no review comments."
  "2026-07-18T19:06:53.842Z",codex-root,"Hosted round 4 accepted CodeRabbit findings: reject transaction step IDs whose surrounding whitespace would diverge execution keys from journal keys, and constrain the invoice documentation example to its open-state compensation precondition. Only pm-4e12 is active for this contract correction."
  "2026-07-18T19:12:19.005Z",codex-root,"Hosted round 4 repairs complete: transaction plans now reject step IDs changed by trimming so execution and every durable journal key remain identical; the SDK invoice example rejects non-open preconditions before applying an open-specific compensation. Both CodeRabbit threads were upvoted, answered inline, and resolved; the review artifact and clean Gemini artifact were reacted to and acknowledged. Verification: focused 15 tests, typecheck, ESLint, zero clones, complexity, 100% docstrings, SDK boundary, token budget, and 311 files / 5,918 tests exact 100/100/100/100 (39,108 statements, 27,504 branches, 7,967 functions, 38,075 lines)."
  "2026-07-18T19:26:40.229Z",codex-root,Exact-head pre-push Greptile review 0f882bf6-7057-4385-8630-a8b038dfc01d completed on 81e4a301 at confidence 4/5 with zero comments. The exact step-identity and documentation-precondition corrections introduce no new findings; the branch is ready for the final hosted review/check cycle.
  "2026-07-18T19:32:19.470Z",codex-root,"Final hosted Greptile review found a valid runtime-boundary P1 on head aed4a6a7: an apply result such as BigInt can fail journal serialization after the domain mutation and then fail the first compensation journal write. Scope is runtime JSON-value validation for every consumer-provided durable result/compensation boundary plus regression coverage proving the mutation is compensated and retry-safe."
  "2026-07-18T19:42:34.204Z",codex-root,"Final hosted P1 repaired: every consumer-provided inspection result, apply result, and compensation pre-state is runtime-cloned through the JSON boundary before journal assignment. Non-serializable values fail with a contextual TypeError while started-step provenance remains durable, so the catch path can write compensating state and reverse the mutation. Regression reproduces a BigInt apply result, proves the journal is compensated with no retained result, proves domain state is restored, retries successfully, and also rejects non-serializable compensation data before apply. Verification: focused SDK+VCS 16 tests pass; typecheck passes; lint, zero clones, static complexity, 100% docstrings, SDK boundary, token budget pass; 311 files / 5,919 tests exact 100/100/100/100 (39,115 statements, 27,504 branches, 7,970 functions, 38,083 lines)."
  "2026-07-18T19:53:20.483Z",codex-root,"Exact-code pre-push Greptile re-review cd1aebe4-75d0-4c46-b130-7156224826a4 completed on fc0da08a at confidence 5/5 with zero comments. It confirmed runtime JSON cloning protects every durable consumer-value boundary, non-serializable values cannot prevent compensation, valid replay semantics remain intact, and the BigInt compensation+retry regression closes the hosted P1. The hosted finding and review were upvoted, answered in the original inline thread with exact-head evidence, and resolved."
  "2026-07-18T19:59:12.541Z",codex-root,"Final hosted round found two valid boundaries on head 559a0dcc: Greptile reproduced non-finite numbers silently becoming null during JSON cloning, and Gemini identified redundant journal writes/transitions for transaction steps that were neither started nor discovered complete. Scope is lossless non-finite rejection plus skip semantics for irrelevant compensation steps, with exact coverage."
  "2026-07-18T20:03:03.339Z",codex-root,"Final hosted fidelity and efficiency findings repaired: the JSON clone replacer rejects every nested non-finite number before it can be normalized to null, preserving exact result semantics and routing the mutation through durable compensation. Compensation now skips steps absent from both started and completed provenance, eliminating false step_compensated transitions and redundant atomic writes while retaining cleanup for discovered-complete steps. Regression covers BigInt, nested NaN, compensated journal state, restored domain state, retry success, and non-serializable pre-state. Verification: focused 16 tests; typecheck; strict lint/zero clones/static/100% docstrings/SDK boundary/token budget; 311 files / 5,919 tests exact 100/100/100/100 (39,120 statements, 27,512 branches, 7,971 functions, 38,087 lines)."
  "2026-07-18T20:20:00.752Z",codex-root,"Exact-code pre-push Greptile re-review e94199d1-be66-47ee-a5f4-0a5a28952020 completed on 48c1f2ae at confidence 5/5 with zero comments. It confirmed nested NaN/infinities and BigInt fail before disk corruption, ordinary compensation cannot strand mutations, irrelevant steps are skipped without losing discovered-complete cleanup, and retry semantics remain correct. Both hosted findings and their review artifacts were upvoted, answered inline with exact-head evidence, and resolved."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T16:49:48.441Z",codex-root,"A transaction journal is a recovery hint, never stronger than current domain inspection: validate lifecycle invariants at load, rebuild completion from inspections, and make every compensation conditional on still owning the exact state it intends to reverse."
